## Part 2: Reference Component — `stripePayment` LWC

Reference implementation of a Payment Element embedded on the Opportunity record page. Triggers on Closed Won stage, processes one-time payments, and writes results back to the Opportunity and Stripe Charge records.

---

### Reference Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `force-app/main/default/lwc/stripePayment/` | The LWC (JS, HTML, CSS, meta.xml) |
| `force-app/main/default/classes/StripePaymentController.cls` | Apex — createPaymentIntent, recordPaymentSuccess |
| `force-app/main/default/classes/ChargeOpportunityLinkerQueueable.cls` | Retry Queueable for Charge → Opportunity linking |

---

### Architecture

```
Opportunity (Closed Won) — record page loads
       │  @wire checks StageName + Payment_Captured__c
       │
       ├─ Payment_Captured__c = true  →  show "Payment Captured" state (no button)
       │
       └─ Payment_Captured__c = false →  show Pay Now button
              │
              ▼  user clicks Pay Now
       Promise.all([createPaymentIntent(), loadScript(Stripe.js)])
              │
              ▼
       StripePaymentController.createPaymentIntent()
              │  Queries Opportunity (Amount, AccountId)
              │  Queries stripeGC__Customer__c by AccountId → params.customer
              │  Queries stripeGC__Stripe_Account__c → publishableKey
              │  Calls v02_CreatePaymentIntents with metadata[opportunity_id]
              │  Returns { publishableKey, clientSecret, amount, customerEmail }
              │
              ▼
       LWC mounts Payment Element (renderedCallback)
              │
              ▼  user completes payment
       stripe.confirmPayment() → paymentIntent.status = 'succeeded'
              │
              ├─ Show success UI immediately
              │
              └─ Fire-and-forget: recordPaymentSuccess(opportunityId, pi_xxx, ch_xxx)
                     │  UPDATE Opportunity: Payment_Captured__c=true, Stripe_Payment_ID__c=pi_xxx
                     │  Try sync Charge link → if not found: enqueue ChargeOpportunityLinkerQueueable
                     └─ getRecordNotifyChange → wire refreshes, button stays hidden
```

---

### Opportunity Fields Used

| Field | API Name | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Stage | `StageName` | Gate component visibility to Closed Won |
| Amount | `Amount` | Payment amount (converted ×100 for Stripe) |
| Name | `Name` | PaymentIntent description + success message |
| Payment Captured | `Payment_Captured__c` | Hides Pay Now button when already paid |
| Stripe Payment ID | `Stripe_Payment_ID__c` | Stores `pi_xxx` after successful payment |

---

### Stripe Account Query

```apex
stripeGC__Stripe_Account__c stripeAccount = [
    SELECT Id, stripeGC__Publishable_Key__c
    FROM stripeGC__Stripe_Account__c
    WHERE stripeGC__Is_Connected__c = true
    WITH USER_MODE
    ORDER BY CreatedDate ASC
    LIMIT 1
];
```

---

### PaymentIntent Params (this component)

```apex
params.accountRecordId = stripeAccount.Id;
params.amount = (Integer)(opp.Amount * 100);
params.r_currency = 'usd';
params.setupFutureUsage = 'off_session';
params.description = 'Payment for Opportunity: ' + opp.Name;
params.performDmlSaveAfterCalls = true;
params.ignoreBillingSyncEventProcessing = true;
params.customer = customers[0].stripeGC__Stripe_Id__c;  // if Account has a Customer
params.receiptEmail = contactEmail;                       // from primary OpportunityContactRole
params.metadata = /* opportunity_id + opportunity_name */;
```

---

### Component State Machine

| State | Condition | What shows |
|---|---|---|
| `showCaptured` | `paymentCaptured && !paymentSuccess` | "Payment Captured" + Stripe Payment ID |
| `showInitial` | `!showPaymentForm && !paymentSuccess && !showError && !paymentCaptured` | Amount summary + Pay Now button |
| `showPaymentForm` | `showPaymentForm = true` | Stripe Payment Element + Complete/Cancel |
| `paymentSuccess` | set after `confirmPayment` succeeds | Success icon + amount collected message |
| `showError` | `initError && !showPaymentForm && !paymentSuccess` | Error message + Try Again button |

---

### Deployment

```bash
sf project deploy start --source-dir force-app -o <your-org-alias>
```

After first deploy: add `stripePayment` component to the Opportunity Record Page via Lightning App Builder (Edit Page > Custom components > drag "Stripe Payment").
